Dogged				KEY:Trait ~ Dogged							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.FaithTrait				PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Dogged]						DESCISPI:YES	DESC:Drawing inspiration from the Cult of the Failed, you refuse to let setbacks stop you, no matter how disastrous. Once per day when you roll a natural 1 on an attack roll, saving throw, skill check, or ability check, you gain a +1 trait bonus on any one roll you attempt before the end of the next round.																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.3
Ecumenical			KEY:Trait ~ Ecumenical						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.SocialTrait				PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Ecumenical]					DESCISPI:YES	DESC:Your childhood in Magnimar (or in a similar cosmopolitan city) taught you to recognize signs of worship of demigods such as empyreal lords. You gain a +2 trait bonus on Knowledge (religion) checks involving entities other than the most influential gods. You also gain a +2 trait bonus on Diplomacy checks to influence worshipers of such entities.																													SOURCEPAGE:p.3
Heretic's Caution	KEY:Trait ~ Heretic's Caution				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.FaithTrait				PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Heretic's Caution]							DESC:You were raised in a faith that did not center on a traditional god or that followed a heretical interpretation of a traditional deity. You learned to deflect attention, especially from ecclesiastical figures. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Bluff checks. This bonus increases to +3 on Bluff checks opposed by religious authorities' Sense Motive checks.								BONUS:SKILL|Bluff|1|TYPE=Trait													SOURCEPAGE:p.3
Imperfect Recall	KEY:Trait ~ Imperfect Recall				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.FaithTrait				PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Imperfect Recall]				DESCISPI:YES	DESC:Your belief in reincarnation, as taught by the Sangpotshi philosophy and in lands that were once Imperial Lung Wa, has been reinforced by personal experience. In moments of great stress, you sometimes experience flashes of déjà vu in which you recall information you don't remember ever having known. Once per day while you are in danger or distracted, you gain a +3 bonus on a single Knowledge skill check.													SOURCEPAGE:p.3
Natural Ritualist	KEY:Trait ~ Natural Ritualist				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.FaithTrait				PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Natural Ritualist]			DESCISPI:YES	DESC:You venerate nature, either by paying homage to your Shoanti totem spirit or by appeasing the kami around you in accordance with Tamashigo. In return, the spirits bless your path. Once per week, you can build a small shrine of natural materials and pay your respects in a ritual that takes 15 minutes. Spellcasters can do this as part of their daily spell preparation. You gain a +2 trait bonus on Knowledge (nature) and Survival checks for 24 hours.			SOURCEPAGE:p.3
Self-Sustaining		KEY:Trait ~ Self-Sustaining					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.FaithTrait				PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.FaithTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Self-Sustaining]				DESCISPI:YES	DESC:As a follower of Razmir, the Prophecies of Kalistrade, or some other tradition that preaches self-reliance, you make a point of not seeking divine aid for minor matters. When you gain this trait, you can cast the chosen spell once per day as a spell-like ability, using your character level as your caster level. Once chosen, this selection can't change.																											SOURCEPAGE:p.3		MULT:YES		STACK:NO		CHOOSE:SPELLS|Create Water|Mending|Purify Food and Drink|Stabilize

